        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 4:07PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 407 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles southeast of Figure Five to 4 miles
northwest of Lavaca to 4 miles south of Huntington. Movement was east
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Alma...                           Charleston...
Shibley...                        Dyer...
Kibler...                         Central City...
Vesta...                          Lonelm...
Ursula...                         Rudy...
Altus...                          Mulberry...
Greenwood...                      Alix...
Bloomer...                        Patterson...
Watalula...                       Meg...
Figure Five...                    Barling...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 2 and 42.
Interstate 540 between mile markers 1 and 13.
Interstate 49 between mile markers 22 and 25.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for west central
Arkansas.</instruction>
